The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Saturday, October 12, 2002 				 Uefa move
																								Nyon, Oct. 11 (Reuters): Uefa punished several European clubs on Friday, including Dutch sides FC Utrecht and PSV Eindhoven, in its drive to stamp out racism in soccer.																								European soccers ruling body ordered Utrecht to play their next Uefa Cup match behind closed doors after crowd trouble in their 3-1 defeat by Polands Legia Warsaw, when a racist banner was brandished by Dutch fans.																								The club said it would consider appealing the decision. 
